pd_0_com_0text: Today is the pre-opening day in the new cafe.
pd_0_com_1text: Being new to the city and opening up the cafe, it's been quite a busy road to this point.
pd_0_com_2text: While there has not been much time to go out and learn about the city, at least you are happy about the cafe itself.
pd_0_com_3text: Everything was stocked up. The store was clean. It was as ready as things could be.
pd_1_com_0text: Well ... Except for the fact that I should probably practice making some drinks.
pd_2_com_0text: You walk behind the drink making counter, looking out at the closed front door with the "Closed" sign hung up.
pd_2_com_1text: Looking behind you, there are various ingredients on the shelves and counter ready to be mixed.
pd_2_com_2text: All that's left is to mix them.
pd_3_com_0text: Well, time to get to work.
pd_3_com_1text: For today, let's just make myself a boba milk tea.
pd_3_com_2text: Should I review how to make drinks?
pd_4_com_1text: No, I'll just wing it and enjoy my drink.
pd_5_com_0text: Ok so first, let's put some ingredients in the blender.
pd_5_com_1text: For the Milk Tea, I need 3 Tea and 2 Sugar.
pd_5_com_2text: Let's just drag them from the shelves into the blender.
pd_5_com_3text: I can tell how full the Blender is based on bars below.
pd_5_com_4text: The blender can only hold up to 6 ingredients.
pd_6_com_0text: You lean closer to inspect the contents of the blender for a moment before nodding and continuing your train of thought.
pd_7_com_0text: That looks good, now I just need to add some boba! I don't know how anyone lives without boba in their milk tea but I can't~
pd_7_com_1text: Ah, before I forget, let's change the milk level. 50% is probably good.
pd_7_com_2text: I can measure it out by dragging the slider or put in the exact value.
pd_7_com_3text: Most customers don't really notice the difference as long as it's within 5% of their request anyway.
pd_7_com_4text: Plus our milk is soy-based so no lactose intolerance issues!
pd_7_com_5text: But in any case, saving 5% milk isn't going to change our budget so there's no point in being stingy.
pd_7_com_6text: Also, if I make a mistake I can just hit the Reset button and start over. Let's try not to do it too often though haha ...
pd_7_com_7text: It's still better than mixing the wrong drink though. That costs me 1 gold every time.
pd_9_com_0text: Ok let's review one more time.
pd_10_com_0text: Now with all the ingredients in the blender and the right milk level, let's hit the mix button!
pd_10_com_1text: When it's finished, let's deliver it by dragging the cup to the customer!
pd_10_com_2text: Well, I'm the only customer for today.
pd_10_com_3text: It's a good thing I write all the recipes I know down into the recipe book. I can select it to review anytime.
pd_11_com_0text: When you take a sip of the drink, you couldn't help but smile at the delicious flavor.
pd_11_com_1text: Yes ... this was why you wanted to become a bobarista in the first place. The joy of giving others a sweet and comforting drink.
pd_12_com_1text: If it has a gray color, that means I must have made a mistake with mixing the ingredients.
pd_12_com_2text: Otherwise ... I might have gotten the topping or milk level incorrect.
pd_12_com_3text: If I could have figured it out, I could throw it away in the trash instead of having the customer complain.
pd_12_com_4text: Well ... Since it's a practice day it's ok. Let's try again.
pd_13_com_0text: With that, all the work planned for the day is completed.
pd_13_com_1text: Tomorrow is a brand new day full of new surprises, events, and customers to meet.
pd_13_com_2text: Hopefully, it'll go as smoothly as today.
pd_13_com_3text: But, until then, you could only wait and see.
pd_14_com_0text: Now, let's make that boba Milk Tea with 50% milk!
pd_15_com_0text: Oh! And I should also collect the money from the customers before I forget. That would be bad.
pd_15_com_1text: I'll remember it at the end of the day but still ... it's not good to leave money just lying around.
